<tr>
<td width="15"><img src="/forums/images/warninglevel.gif" width="16" height="16" Alt="Qinnyinya's Warning Level: 0"></td><td align="left" nowrap><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Level: 0 </font></td>
</tr>
</table>
</td></tr></table>
		<br>
		</td></tr></table>
	<!-- Postbit User Info -->
</td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#666699" width="100%" valign="top">
	
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 11-24-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">02:01 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">It all depends on what you want to do at 65+ as to whether your gear will get you there.  If you are going to 2-box with your monk in lower XP zones, you will be fine.  If you want to raid and progress through PoP/GoD/OoW, you will need better gear, but it will come as you raid most likely.<br />
<br />
The things I look for in upgrades these days are mana regen (not capped yet), focus effects, mana, resists, hps, AC, and stamina.  A wise dorf named Chowar told me long ago to not worry about wisdom on gear, as it will come naturally as you progress.  At the time I though the old guy was off his rocker, but it turns out he was right.<br />
<br />
As a point of reference, with my gear I can easily keep up in WoS or lower zones.  I struggle a little in MPG and the higher GoD instanced (Vxed and Tipt) and pretty much need a very solid tank to survive in those zones.  I get eaten up by AE's and rampage on most of the "mid-range" raid encounters (most of the epic 1.5 fights, etc) and the tough single group fights (Discordling Warfiend in WoS tore me up badly with rampage last night).  I have been pretty effective in the lower PoP progression fights so far.<br />
<br />
There are a lot of inexpensive bazaar upgrades for you.  There are a lot of OoW drops that are pretty cheap these days.  Even some of the LDoN drops would be nice upgrades for you.  Off the top of my head, Greaves of the Orcish Master, Architect's Bejeweled Chestplate, Facemask of Frozen Mana, Armguards of Rependence (sp), the cleric only shoulders with FT2 and Boon of the Pious, the hands from the same WoS mob that drops the cleric shoulders, Boots of Slaughter, and all of the Magnetized armor (or better yet charged Magnetized) from OoW.  There are several nice range slot items from OoW with nice effects or mana regen on them.  The random drop WoS face item would be nice too (and I am still waiting on that one...lol).  PoP ornate wrists, or better yet OoW ornate wrists, would be good for the mana regen.<br />
<br />
Just some thoughts for you to look into.  You need to be 60+ for some of it, 65+ for other items I listed.  Some is no-drop, some is quested (and the quest drops are from normal XP mobs in various zones).  There is all kinds of stuff out there these days that is obtainable without a major raid.<br />
<br />
And FYI, the Tainted Heartstone is an awesome charm item for the non-PoP raider.  All you need to do is max your languages to get full stats off of it.  I don't know if it is a bug, but I was getting full stats (with maxed languages) on my level 20 at the time druid, so the recommended level on the thing seems to be broken.  I highly recommend picking one up if you are not doing PoP pregression and empowering your PoP charm.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1070975"><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~sdave33/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/qinny.jpg" border="0" alt=""></a>
</font></p></p>
	<p><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><i>Last edited by Qinnyinya on 11-24-2004 at 02:05 PM</i></font></p>
	</td></tr></table>
